Client Setup & Domain Join
1. Acquire Installation Media

Navigate to the Microsoft Evaluation Center.

Download the Windows 11 Enterprise ISO.

2. Create Virtual Machine (VMware)

In VMware Workstation Pro, click File > New Virtual Machine.

Select Typical > Select Installer disc image file (ISO).

VM Configuration details:

Name: Win11-Client-01

Encryption: Select "Only the files needed to support a TPM are encrypted."

Encryption Password: Password123

Disk Size: 64 GB (Windows 11 minimum requirement).

Hardware: Leave defaults (4096 MB RAM, 2 CPU Cores).

Click Finish.

3. Install Windows 11

Start the VM. Click inside the black screen and press any key when prompted to "boot from CD or DVD."

Windows Setup flow: Select English > Click through until you reach account sign-in.

Select Sign-in options > Domain join instead.

Local Administrator Setup:

User: LocalAdmin

Password: Password123

Complete privacy questions and finish setup.

Optional: If you missed the device rename step during setup, go to Settings > System > Rename and set the name to Client-01.

4. Configure Networking
Set DNS

On the VM, press Windows Key + R > type ncpa.cpl (Opens Network Connections).

Right-click Ethernet0 > Properties.

Select Internet Protocol Version 4 (TCP/IP) > Properties.

IP Settings:

IP Address: Keep 'Obtain Automatically'.

DNS Server: Select 'Use the following DNS server addresses'.

Preferred DNS: 192.168.242.10

Click OK > Close.

Verify Connectivity

Open a Terminal/Command Prompt and run the following command:

code
Powershell
download
content_copy
expand_less
ping ad.lab

✅ Success Criteria:
You should receive a reply from the Domain Controller. This confirms DNS is resolving correctly.

5. Join the Domain

Go to Settings > System > About.

Click Domain or Workgroup.

Click Change to rename this computer or change its domain.

Domain Configuration:

Member of: Select Domain.

Domain Name: ad.lab

Credentials: Use Administrator and your domain admin password.

Restart the computer when prompted.

6. Move Client-01 to Workstations OU

Note: When a machine joins the domain, AD places it in the default "Computers" container. GPOs linked to specific OUs (like Workstations) will not apply until the object is moved.

Log into your Server/Domain Controller.

Open Active Directory Users and Computers.

Open the Computers container.

Drag Client-01 into the Workstations OU (Located inside DemoCorp_Root).

Return to the client machine (Client-01), open Command Prompt, and run:

code
Cmd
download
content_copy
expand_less
gpupdate /force

✅ Success Criteria:
The command prompt should return: "Computer policy update has completed successfully."
